---

<BaseLayout
  title="BreederHQ vs EasyKeeper: The Honest 2026 Comparison"
  description="BreederHQ vs EasyKeeper compared on pricing, species coverage, dairy tracking, marketplace, buyer portal, and mobile for goat breeders. Verified July 2026."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <script is:inline type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(articleSchema)} />
  <script is:inline type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(competitorReviewGraph)} />

  <a href="#main-content" class="skip-link sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:absolute focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:z-50 focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:bg-white focus:text-black focus:shadow-lg focus:rounded">
    Skip to content
  </a>

  <main id="main-content">
    <nav class="breadcrumb py-4 px-4 bg-gray-50" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2 max-w-4xl mx-auto text-sm">
        <li><a href="/" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Home</a></li>
        <li class="text-gray-400">›</li>
        <li><a href="/compare" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Compare</a></li>
        <li class="text-gray-400">›</li>
        <li aria-current="page" class="text-gray-600">BreederHQ vs EasyKeeper</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="py-20 px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">BreederHQ vs EasyKeeper: The Honest 2026 Comparison for Goat Breeders</h1>

        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">Published: July 1, 2026 &middot; Last verified against easykeeper.com: July 1, 2026</p>

        <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          EasyKeeper is the goat specialist, web-only, with the multi-year dairy specialist&apos;s edge on age-adjusted 305-day calc, DHIR programmatic pull, batch-session milking capture, and lactation persistence calculations. BreederHQ ships a mature dairy production surface today (milking records with butterfat / protein / SCC / MUN / lactose, lactation cycles, DHIA with bulk CSV import and saved presets, Linear Appraisal, peak-yield tracking with days-to-peak, herd dashboards, native mobile) plus multi-species coverage, a transactional public marketplace, per-buyer client portal, and an embed widget for your own website. Both are used by real goat breeders. Here is the honest version of when each one wins.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a href="https://accounts.breederhq.com/register" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 rounded-md bg-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] text-white font-semibold hover:bg-[hsl(24,95%,48%)] transition">
            Start 14-day free trial
          </a>
          <a href="/pricing" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 rounded-md border-2 border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-semibold hover:border-gray-400 transition">
            See BreederHQ pricing
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TL;DR -->
    <section class="py-12 px-4 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <aside class="bg-white border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] p-6 rounded shadow-sm" role="complementary" aria-label="Page summary">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">TL;DR</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            <strong>Pick EasyKeeper if</strong> you run a goats-only operation and the specific EasyKeeper strengths matter most: age-adjusted 305-day lactation calc, programmatic DHIR registry pull (not just CSV import), single-session batch milking capture UI, and lactation persistence calculations. EasyKeeper is the multi-year dairy-goat specialist, has approximately 90,000 goats under management (self-reported June 2026), and has a strong community reputation. Essentials is $19/month or $209/year; Performance is $27/month or $297/year.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Pick BreederHQ if</strong> DHIA CSV import satisfies your test-day workflow (BreederHQ ships bulk CSV import with saved per-tenant mapping presets, plus milking records with butterfat / protein / SCC / MUN / lactose, lactation cycles, Linear Appraisal with public-visibility toggle, and a herd dashboard with lactation curves, top producers, and mastitis-watch), and you also want: multi-species coverage (nine species in one account), native iOS and Android mobile capture for the kidding pen and milking stand, a public transactional marketplace at marketplace.breederhq.com, a per-buyer client portal, per-litter and per-kid financial attribution with quarterly tax export, an embed widget that auto-updates your own farm website, herd-level CAE / CL / Johne&apos;s status with private certificate binding, and first-class scrapie compliance (premises ID, tattoo placement, CVI, movement logs). Dairy is not a roadmap gap; it is a shipped surface with specific parity boundaries called out honestly in the table below.
          </p>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Screenshot placeholder -->
    <section class="py-8 px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <figure class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8 bg-gray-50 text-center">
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-2">Illustration</div>
          <div class="text-lg text-gray-700 font-medium">BreederHQ mobile app: kidding pen weight capture</div>
          <figcaption class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-3">Weight entry from the mobile app during kidding, with body condition scoring, notes, and photo capture in one flow. Data lands in the herd record and rolls up to per-kid growth curves.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Comparison table -->
    <section class="py-16 px-4">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Side-by-side: BreederHQ vs EasyKeeper</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
          Publicly verifiable facts only, sourced from easykeeper.com and breederhq.com. Verified July 1, 2026. Vendors change pricing and feature scope. Confirm on each site before committing.
        </p>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-white shadow-sm">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead class="bg-gray-100 text-left">
              <tr>
                <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Capability</th>
                <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">EasyKeeper</th>
                <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">BreederHQ</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Entry price</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Essentials $19/mo ($209/yr); Performance $27/mo ($297/yr)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">See <a href="/pricing" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">pricing page</a>. FOUNDER50: 50% off Pro or Enterprise for 12 months.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Free trial length</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">30 days, no credit card</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">14 days</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Species supported</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Goats only (dairy, meat, fiber, hobby/specialty)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">9 (dogs, cats, horses, goats, rabbits, sheep, alpacas, llamas, cattle)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Milk yield / lactation tracking</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes, mature depth. Performance tier includes milk production and batch entry.</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes: milking records with butterfat, protein, SCC, MUN, lactose; lactation cycles with dry-off; 305-day standardized lactation calc (simplified, without age adjustment); native mobile capture on iOS and Android.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Age-adjusted 305-day lactation</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes (with age adjustment)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Simplified calc without age adjustment</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Peak yield tracking</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Advertised</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes: peak daily production, peak date, days-to-peak; herd-level averages (avg peak, avg days-to-peak)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Lactation persistence calculations</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Advertised</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Not shipped</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">DHIA test-day recording</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes: test weight, butterfat/protein/lactose, SCC, MUN, lab, certificate URL, document attachment</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">DHIA bulk CSV import with saved mapping presets</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Not publicly advertised</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes: per-row outcome reporting, per-tenant header-name-keyed presets so subsequent imports auto-match</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">DHIR programmatic registry pull</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes (advertised)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Not shipped (CSV import path only)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Linear Appraisal (ADGA)</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Not publicly advertised as a feature</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes: final score (0-99), classification passthrough, four category scores, arbitrary trait scores JSON, bulk CSV import, appraisal trend chart, per-row public-visibility toggle for marketplace</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Herd-level dairy dashboard</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes (advertised as production records at a glance)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes: lactation curves, top producers ranking, mastitis-watch (SCC), DHIA and appraisal rollups, dedicated dairy-operations preset dashboard</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Batch session milking entry (multiple animals, one timestamp)</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes (Performance-tier feature)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Bulk import (each record carries its own timestamp) yes; single-session batch capture UI not shipped</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Herd health status (CAE, CL, Johne&apos;s)</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Not publicly advertised as first-class</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes: tenant-level HerdHealthStatus with private certificate binding, per-animal test history</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Scrapie compliance (premises ID, tattoo placement, CVI, movement logs)</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Not publicly advertised as first-class</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes, first-class: premises ID, herd prefix, structured tattoo placement, CVI certificates, movement/transport logs</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">FAMACHA + FEC + FECRT as canonical entries</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Not publicly advertised</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes: FAMACHA scores, fecal egg count, and FECRT captured as canonical TraitDefinition + AnimalTraitEntry rows with trend charts</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
